You are working on a React Native CLI project (no Expo) using HeroUI Native as the UI library.

# Key Rules

## HeroUI Native uses COMPOUND COMPONENTS — not flat props

WRONG:
- `<Input label="Email" errorMessage="Required" isInvalid />`
- `<Button isLoading={true}>Submit</Button>`
- `<Alert variant="danger">Error</Alert>`
- `<Avatar name="John" />`

CORRECT:
- `<TextField isInvalid><Label><Label.Text>Email</Label.Text></Label><Input .../><FieldError>Required</FieldError></TextField>`
- `<Button isDisabled={loading}>{loading ? <Spinner /> : <Button.Label>Submit</Button.Label>}</Button>`
- `<Alert status="danger"><Alert.Indicator /><Alert.Content><Alert.Description>Error</Alert.Description></Alert.Content></Alert>`
- `<Avatar size="lg"><Avatar.Fallback>JD</Avatar.Fallback></Avatar>`

## Imports

Use path aliases: @api/, @components/, @hooks/, @navigation/, @screens/, @store/, @theme/, @utils/
For types: use @app-types/ (NOT @types/ — conflicts with npm @types)

## State Management

- Zustand for client state (auth, preferences) — persisted via MMKV
- TanStack Query for server/API state — handles cache, refetch, loading/error
- DO NOT store API responses in Zustand — use TanStack Query

## API Pattern

- Axios client at src/api/client.ts (auto token + 401 refresh)
- Endpoints at src/api/endpoints/<feature>.ts
- Query hooks at src/api/queries/<feature>.ts using useQuery/useMutation
- Types at src/api/types/<feature>.ts

## Environment

- Use `import Config from 'react-native-config'` for env vars
- Base URL: Config.API_BASE_URL
- Files: .env.development, .env.staging, .env.production

## Conventions

- Named exports (no default except App.tsx)
- Screens in screens/<feature>/ folders
- TypeScript strict mode
- Zod for form validation (src/utils/validators.ts)
- Dark/light theme via Uniwind.setTheme()
